==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morintannic
<hw>Mo`rin*tan"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Morus</ets> fustic + E. <ets>tannic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, a variety of
tannic acid extracted from fustic (<spn>Chlorophora tinctoria</spn>,
formerly <spn>Maclura tinctoria</spn> and <spn>Morus tinctoria</spn>) as
a yellow crystalline substance; -- called also
<altname>maclurin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morion</ent>⟦br⟧
